[The following question is from a human user]

Answer this question: Which actress was voted Miss Greenwich Village in 1942?

response:
Lauren Bacall was voted Miss Greenwich Village in 1942.

This occurred when she was still a teenager (born in 1924, she would have been about 17-18 years old) and before she became a famous Hollywood actress. She was working as a model and theater usher in New York at the time, before her breakthrough film role opposite Humphrey Bogart in "To Have and Have Not" (1944).
